{{Quote|I wanted to be you. Sam Wilson. Because that guy, that guy won't ever give up. That pressure, that responsibility you talk about, I want that, too, man.|Joaquín Torres to [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Captain '''Joaquín Torres''' is a [[United States Air Force]] intelligence officer and a friend of [[Sam Wilson]]. In the aftermath of the [[Blip]], Torres met and befriended Sam Wilson during one of his Air Force missions. Torres aided Wilson during his [[Flag Smashers' Political Ultimatum|conflict]] with the [[Flag Smashers]]. At the climax of their campaign, Wilson became the new [[Captain America]], having passed his [[EXO-7 Falcon|old wingsuit]] and the mantle of '''Falcon''' to Torres.

In [[2027]], Falcon and Captain America successfully intercepted an illegal sale of [[adamantium]] organized by [[SERPENT]] in [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]. In the aftermath of an [[Attack on President Ross|attack]] on newly-elected President [[Thaddeus Ross]] at the [[White House]] during the [[Celestial Island World Summit]], Torres and Wilson investigated [[Camp Echo One]] in [[West Virginia]] and discovered that [[Leader]] used mind control on [[Isaiah Bradley]] to attack the president and later would join Captain America in [[Battle of Celestial Island|stopping]] two mind-controlled pilots from attacking the [[Japan]]ese fleet near [[Celestial Island]] to prevent a war between Japan and the [[United States]]. Although successful, Falcon was injured in the process. While Torres eventually recovered, Wilson recruited him as an [[Avengers|Avenger]].

==Biography==
{{MD|Joaquín Torres (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Watching Heroes====
{{Quote|Where I grew up, I only ever got to see heroes online or on TV. They always felt so far away. And I kept thinking maybe if I get out of [[Miami]], maybe one day I could be..."<br>"Don't say [[Ant-Man]].|Joaquín Torres and [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Joaquín Torres was born and raised in [[Miami]], [[Florida]] and was a fan of {{WPS|University of Miami}} football. Torres took a particular interest in watching various superheroes, and would aspire to one day be just like them. Specifically, Torres idolized [[Sam Wilson]], also known as Falcon, as Torres admired his ability to never give up despite having no powers.{{Ref|CABNW}}

===Air Force Career===
====Surviving the Snap====
{{Quote|[[Flag Smashers|They]] think that the world was better during the [[Snap|Blip]]. Trust me, it wasn't.|Joaquín Torres to [[Sam Wilson]]|New World Order}}
In [[2018]], Torres survived the [[Snap]]. For the next five years, he witnessed firsthand the hardships it brought.{{Ref|TFaTWS101}}

====[[Rescue of Captain Vassant]]====
[[File:First Lt. Torres.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres assisting [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] during the rescue]]
{{Quote|All right, heads up! You're about to fly into [[Libya]]n airspace."<br>"And I assume they have a problem with that."<br>"Yeah, yeah. A big problem.|Joaquín Torres and [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]]|New World Order}}
In [[2024]], Torres teamed up with and befriended his hero, [[Sam Wilson]], to rescue [[Vassant]], who was kidnapped by the terrorist organization known as the [[LAF]] before they were able to get him over the [[Tunisia]]n border where the U.S. could not be seen operating. While driving a Humvee, he helped assist Wilson from the ground and watched as the mission was successful. He then leapt in the air in gleeful excitement.{{Ref|TFaTWS101}}

====Discussing Flag Smashers====
[[File:Sam Wilson & Torres.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres tries to help [[Sam Wilson]] fix [[Redwing]]]]
{{Quote|You see these guys? These are the guys you gotta worry about. I've been stumbling onto their manifestos on message boards. They call themselves [[Flag Smashers]]."<br>"Is that a new thing? Bad guys give themselves bad names.|Joaquin Torres and [[Sam Wilson]]|New World Order}}
Afterwards, he and Wilson went to a café together in Tunisia: Torres tried to help Wilson fix [[Redwing]], but Wilson told him he had it. Two locals then walked up and thanked Wilson for his role in bringing about the [[Blip]].
[[File:Torres talks about the Blip.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres talks about the [[Flag Smashers]]' goal]]
Torres then told Wilson about a new terrorist group called the [[Flag Smashers]], who believed life was better during the Blip, and showed him their symbol on his phone. Torres then told Wilson that conspiracy theories had popped up online about [[Steve Rogers]] living on the [[Moon|moon]] as the general public didn't know what happened to him. Wilson told him not to believe everything online. When Wilson got up to leave, Torres asked why he was going to [[Washington, D.C.]], only for Wilson to smile at him and say "moon stuff."{{Ref|TFaTWS101}}

====[[Robbery of Gasel Bank]]====
[[File:Torres Flag Smasher Mask.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres tries to infiltrate the [[Flag Smashers]]]]
{{Quote|I don't know how jurisdiction works [[Switzerland|here]], but I'mma have to place you under arrest.|Joaquín Torres to [[Dovich]]|New World Order}}
Deciding to go investigate himself, Torres travelled to [[Switzerland]] in order to track down the [[Flag Smashers]] and found a group of people sliding on masks. Confused, Torres put one on, but soon realized that he had wandered into the middle of a bank robbery led by the same terrorist organization he was searching for.
[[File:Dovich & Torres.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres is knocked unconscious by [[Dovich]]]]
A local policeman attempted to arrest the masked Torres, but he easily got away from him. He then filmed a [[Dovich|Flag Smasher]] knocking away another policeman with superhuman force. Torres tossed aside the mask and brought out his handgun, confronting the terrorist. Torres tried to arrest the terrorist, but was no match for him and was knocked unconscious. After regaining consciousness, Torres contacted [[Sam Wilson]], updating him on what happened with the Flag Smashers.{{Ref|TFaTWS101}}

====Heading to Munich====
[[File:Torres & Wilson.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Sam Wilson]] prepare to depart]]
{{Quote|We're at two hundred feet. It's too low for a chute."<br>"I don't need it anyway."<br>"You sure about that?|Joaquín Torres and [[Bucky Barnes]]|The Star-Spangled Man}}
Returning to the [[United States of America]] to the USAF base, Torres met up with [[Sam Wilson]], who he was helping travel to [[Munich]]. Torres noticed Wilson looking at a poster of the new [[John Walker|new Captain America]] and expressed that he seemed like a good person. As the two headed to the aircraft, Wilson thanked Torres for his help.
[[File:The Falcon and the Winter Soldier 36.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Sam Wilson]] flying into [[Germany]]]]
They were joined by [[Bucky Barnes]] on the flight to [[Germany]], and once they reached the drop zone, Torres told Wilson to get ready to deploy. Torres opened the door and watched as Wilson jumped out and flew to his destination. Barnes asked about a parachute but Torres explained that they were too low to use a parachute. Barnes decided that he did not need one, and Torres was surprised to watch as Barnes ripped off his sleeve and jumped out of the aircraft, only to crash onto the ground.{{Ref|TFaTWS102}}

====Helping Sam Wilson====
[[File:Torres & Sam.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres regroups with [[Sam Wilson]] in [[Latvia]]]]
{{Quote|All we can do now is sit tight and just chill. Sometimes, there's nothing to do until there's something to do.|Joaquín Torres to [[Sam Wilson]]|Truth}}Upon being asked by [[Sam Wilson]] to look up a woman named [[Donya Madani]], Torres called Wilson telling him that she died and that she was residing in [[Riga]], [[Latvia]], prompting Wilson to travel there for clues.{{Ref|TFaTWS103}} Later, Torres met with Wilson and [[Bucky Barnes]] at the former [[Latvian GRC Resettlement Camp]] in Riga. Torres greeted Barnes and mentioned to him that he noticed he had gotten his sleeve back after ripping it off on the aircraft in [[Munich]], although Barnes ignored him and left. 
[[File:Joaquin Torres (GRC Resettlement Camp).png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres is given the [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]] from [[Sam Wilson]]]]
Torres revealed that the international incident with [[John Walker]] was being dealt with, while noticing Wilson's [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]] were broken. Torres asked how they were damaged, but Wilson did not answer, instead enquiring about what there was for them to do. Torres explained that with [[Karli Morgenthau]] in hiding, all they could do was standby and wait. As Wilson walked away, Torres told him that he forgot to take the wings, but Wilson responded by telling Torres to keep them, passing the Falcon mantle onto him.{{Ref|TFaTWS105}}
[[File:Torres calls Sam.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres informs [[Sam Wilson]] of a new attack]]
Two months later,{{Ref|MSTB}} Torres video-called Wilson to inform him of the results he obtained from the scans that Wilson had asked him to investigate. Torres explained that there was a connection in what he had discovered, as all of the locations that were pinged proceeded to be attacked by the [[Flag Smashers]]. Torres then revealed that a new ping was discovered over [[New York City]], leading them to suspect it was the next target for the Flag Smashers. Wilson thanked Torres for the intel and told him he would handle the situation.{{Ref|TFaTWS105}}

====New Mantle====
[[File:TF&TWS Pilot EP6.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Torres watching [[Sam Wilson]] give a speech]]
While at the USAF base, Torres watched the news from his laptop after the [[Flag Smashers]] [[Attack on the GRC|attack]] on the [[Global Repatriation Council]]. Torres witnessed as [[Sam Wilson]], who had now taken on the mantle of Captain America and defeated the Flag Smashers, spoke to the council. Torres proudly watched on as his friend told the council how they could better help the world, as well as talk about the difficulties he will face as the new Captain America.{{Ref|TFaTWS106}}

===The New Falcon===
====[[Skirmish at Catedral de Santo Ramos]]====
[[File:Joaquin as the guy in the chair.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres assists [[Captain America]] on a mission]]
{{Quote|You can't be in two places at once."<br>"All right, this time. But don't get yourself killed."<br>"No dying. Copy that.|Joaquín Torres and [[Captain America]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Torres repaired and painted [[Sam Wilson]]'s previous [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]], and donned his own costume to operate as the new Falcon. Still serving in the [[United States Air Force|Air Force]], Torres continued to work directly with Wilson, assisting him on missions. In [[2027]], Torres oversaw Captain America fight [[SERPENT]], who had stolen a package, but Torres did not know what was inside, as it was classified.
[[File:Falcon (Brave New World).png|{{AltFloat}}|Falcon recovers the canister from [[SERPENT]]]]
Torres informed an occupied Captain America that three SERPENT members escaping with the canister. Captain America knew that Torres wanted to suit up, so he approved, telling Torres not to get killed. Falcon exited the aircraft and pursued the three SERPENT members escaping on motorbikes. Falcon shot out the tire on one of the motorbikes, causing all three to crash. Falcon neutralised the mercenaries and the celebrated to himself, although he wished someone had witnessed him. Falcon then reported that he had secured the canister.
[[File:Captain America and Joaquin Torres.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Falcon jokes around with [[Captain America]]]]
Falcon regrouped with Captain America back at [[Catedral de Santo Ramos]], bragging about how he did not die during the mission. Falcon then claimed on making Captain America's old costume look new, but Captain America messed with him by saying he was wearing it wrong. Captain America stated that Falcon did look good, and the latter then asked if he could be introduced to [[Ant-Man]] and learn how to do an aerial kick, but Captain America said no to both. Captain America said that he knew [[Isaiah Bradley|someone]] who would train Falcon, although from Falcon's reaction, Captain America did not think they would get along.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Meeting Isaiah Bradley====
[[File:Joaquín and Sam.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres is introduced to [[Isaiah Bradley]]]]
{{Quote|Who's the pretty boy?"<br>"'Pretty boy'? [[Captain America|You]] didn't tell gramps about me? I'm the new Falcon.|[[Isaiah Bradley]] and Joaquín Torres|Captain America: Brave New World}}
[[Sam Wilson]] brought Torres to [[Baltimore]] and introduced him [[Isaiah Bradley]]. Torres made jokes about Bradley being old, doubting what he could teach them, but Torres then witnessed Bradley send a punching bag flying with one hit. Torres realized who Bradley was and praised him for his service. Torres watched Wilson train with Bradley, but they were interrupted when Wilson got a call from President [[Thaddeus Ross]], leaving Torres to make jokes about Bradley's phone.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====[[Celestial Island World Summit]]====
[[File:Joaquin, Sam & Isaiah.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres with [[Sam Wilson]] and [[Isaiah Bradley]]]]
{{Quote|I don't care if it is [[Thaddeus Ross|Ross]] in charge. We are guests of honor at the [[White House]], man! When does that ever happen?|Joaquín Torres|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Torres, [[Sam Wilson]], and [[Isaiah Bradley]] were invited by [[Thaddeus Ross]] to be guests of honor to the [[White House]]. The three were picked up by a limousine, and during the drive, Torres suggested that they celebrate their special treatment, even though Ross was in charge. Once they arrived at the White House, Torres took a selfie with the three of them and sent it to Bradley, who he had to teach about {{WPS|Airdrop}}.
[[File:Torres saves the French President.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres protects the President of [[France]]]]
After Wilson met with Ross, he revealed that Ross wanted him to rebuild the [[Avengers]], which Torres was exited by. Torres sat through Ross' summit, where he and Wilson were applauded for their efforts in recovering the [[adamantium]]. The summit was interrupted when Bradley suddenly got up, attacked an agent and attempted to shoot Ross, along with a few other agents. Torres and Wilson dealt with the situation, with Torres stopping some of the attackers and getting the [[France|French]] President to safety.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Investigating the Attack====
[[File:Torres investigates.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres investigates the [[White House]] [[Attack on President Ross|attack]]]]
{{Quote|I think I committed treason and espionage, but I made it into the [[White House]]'s CCTV system. What am I lookin' for?|Joaquín Torres to [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
The next day, [[Sam Wilson]] asked Torres to hack into the [[White House]]'s surveillance system to investigate what happened. Torres discovered Bradley and the other attackers' phones flashing before the [[Celestial Island World Summit|summit]]. Wilson speculated about their encounter with [[SERPENT]] being planned by someone to get all of them at the White House. Wilson ended the call by tasking Torres with looking into [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]].{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Going Rogue====
[[File:Joaquín Torres at his computer.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Sam Wilson]] decide to go rogue]]
{{Quote|You don't have to come with me."<br>"Duh, I know. That's what makes it so noble.|[[Sam Wilson]] and Joaquín Torres|Captain America: Brave New World}}
When Wilson returned to his office, Torres learned that he had been [[Attack on Sam Wilson|attacked]] by [[Sidewinder]], who he defeated. Wilson gave Sidewinder's phone to Torres for him to trace, and as he did, Torres revealed that [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]] was a former [[Black Widows|Black Widow]]. Torres traced the call to [[Camp Echo One]], so Wilson decided to go investigate, disobeying [[Thaddeus Ross]]' orders.
[[File:Joaquin Torres (Brave New World).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Sam Wilson]] discuss the [[Leader|buyer]]]]
Wilson told Torres he did not have to come with him, but he did anyways, and the two packed their suits and left. As they headed to [[West Virginia]], Torres played on his burner phone while Wilson drove. Torres learned that the [[Joint Base Anacostia–Bolling|prison]] Bradley was in had been attacked, and the other shooters were killed. Torres asked if they should turn back, but Wilson claimed it was the [[Leader|buyer]] knowing they were close to figuring out who they were, so they kept going forward.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====[[Infiltration into Camp Echo One]]====
[[File:Captain America Brave New World Teaser Trailer (63).png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Captain America|Wilson]] explore [[Camp Echo One]]]]
{{Quote|Being right always go like this?"<br>"Most of the time.|Joaquín Torres and [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Arriving outside of [[Camp Echo One]], Torres and Wilson stealthily made their way inside without being detected. Torres and Wilson searched the inside of the prison, but found it completely empty. They discovered a lab, where Torres found out that the flashing lights planted commands in [[Isaiah Bradley]] and the others, which could be triggered by the ''{{WPS|Mr. Blue}}'' song.
[[File:Joaquin and Sam.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Sam Wilson]] are found by [[Leader]]]]
The two were then joined by [[Leader]], who revealed that he was the one behind everything as part of his revenge plan against [[Thaddeus Ross]] for imprisoning and using him for years. Leader told them to not interfere with his plans, and made his escape while a group of mind controlled soldiers arrived. Torres and Wilson managed to neutralize the soldiers and chased after Leader. They were stopped by more soldiers, but [[Ruth Bat-Seraph]] arrived and saved them.
[[File:Joaquin and Sam arrested.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres and [[Sam Wilson|Wilson]] are arrested by the [[FBI]]]]
As they explained the situation to Bat-Seraph outside, Torres and Wilson were arrested by [[FBI]] agents, under the orders of Ross. Torres questioned Wilson if being right usually went this way, which Wilson replied it did most of the time. As Bat-Seraph tried to get them freed, ''Mr. Blue'' began playing and the agents became mind controlled and opened fire. Torres, Wilson and Bat-Seraph quickly ran to their car and drove away, managing to escape.
[[File:Torres overrides Leader's mind control.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres overrides [[Leader]]'s mind control]]
The three headed to [[Norfolk]], where they grouped up with [[Dennis Dunphy]] and his team. Torres used a terminal and plugged in the data he obtained from Camp Echo One to create a program that would block out Leader's mind control. Bat-Seraph wondered if Leader had already mind controlled someone at their base, so Torres played the song to see if anyone would be activated, but no one was. Torres completed the program, and they left after Wilson spoke to [[Sidewinder]], who revealed Leader's full plan.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====[[Battle of Celestial Island]]====
[[File:Falcon and Captain America.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Falcon and [[Captain America]] are deployed]]
{{Quote|We need to get the [[Japan]]ese out of the air. Stay close and don't get yourself killed."<br>"No dying, copy that.|[[Captain America]] and Falcon|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Falcon and [[Captain America]] suited up and flew to [[Celestial Island]], where [[Thaddeus Ross]] was onboard the {{WPS|USS Milius}}. Falcon shut down [[Leader]]'s system as Captain America tried to warn Ross about Leader's plans, but they discovered that two pilots had been controlled and attacked the [[Japan]]ese fleet. Ross told Falcon and Captain America to stop the pilots, so they rushed outside and went to help the Japanese pilots.
[[File:Falcon flying by Tiamut.png|{{AltFloat}}|Falcon saves the {{WPS|USS Milius}} from being hit]]
As they took to they sky, Captain America once again told Falcon not to get killed. Falcon and Captain America attempted to tell the Japanese pilots to return to their fleet, but they did not listen. [[Whiskey]] and [[Jackal]] continued to open fire, which resulted in the Japanese fleet to return fire, so Falcon and Captain America acted quickly to destroy their missiles. When Captain America disabled Whiskey's jet, Falcon rushed to get him out of the cockpit and to safety.
[[File:Falcon rescue.png|{{AltFloat}}|Falcon is rescued after falling from the sky]]
Falcon wondered why the Japanese fleet were still firing at them, so Captain America explained that Ross had not told them who was really behind the attacks. Falcon kept the Japanese pilots distracted, but when Jackal fired his last two missiles, Falcon destroyed one of them. Falcon went to get the other one, but Captain America warned him to not. Falcon did not listen and destroyed the missile, but was hit in the blast, causing him to fall out of the sky and into the water, where he was recovered by search and rescue.{{Ref|CABNW}}

====Hospitalized====
[[File:Joaquin Torres in surgery.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres' heart is restarted during surgery]]
{{Quote|You never messed up like I have. You never got shot out of the sky and nosedived into the Indian Ocean. You're always on point.|Joaquín Torres to [[Sam Wilson]]|Captain America: Brave New World}}
Torres was in critical condition from the battle and was rushed to the hospital, where they immediately put him into surgery, in which the doctors had to restart his heart. Torres survived and remained in the hospital as he recovered. [[Sam Wilson]] visited Torres, jokingly saying that Falcon had awakened.
[[File:Captain America recruits Falcon.png|{{AltFloat}}|Torres is the first recruit into the [[Avengers]]]]
Torres apologized for messing up during the [[Battle of Celestial Island|battle]], and compared himself with Wilson, who he claimed never messed up. Wilson explained it was because he always he had pressure on him to not let anyone down. Torres revealed that he always idolized Wilson and expressed that he wanted that pressure. Wilson taught Torres how to do his aerial kick, and told Torres to be ready, as he intended to rebuild the [[Avengers]]. Excited by this, Torres asked Wilson about contacting [[Wakanda]] to get him new [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]].{{Ref|CABNW}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Expand}}
*'''[[EXO-7 Falcon]] Capabilities''': Although Torres does not possess any innate powers, he is granted several abilities through his use of the EXO-7 Falcon given by [[Sam Wilson]].
**'''Superhuman Speed''': With the thrusters on Torres' wings, he could reach very fast speeds.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': Torres could also maneuver in the air to dodge incoming attacks from his enemies.
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': The suit worn by Torres granted him increased stamina. This stamina allowed him to fly through the air without having to use a lot of energy to do so.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': Along with agility, Torres could dodge many obstacles while using the wings.
**'''Enhanced Vision''': The goggles used by Torres allow him to view multiple spectrums and see objects that are either too far away or too small to be seen by the naked eye.
**'''Flight''': Using his specialized winged jetpack, Joaquín Torres is able to fly at high speeds with an enhanced degree of maneuverability and agility similar to that of an actual falcon.

===Abilities===
*'''Expert Martial Artist''': Due to extensive military training, Torres became a capable combatant. He easily overpowered a policeman with a jiu-jitsu movement.
*'''Expert Marksman''': Torres is skilled in wielding firearms, particularly pistols.
*'''Expert Acrobat''': ''To be added''
*'''Expert Pilot''': ''To be added''
*'''Expert Investigator''': Having found many [[Flag Smashers]] pop-ups, Torres took it upon himself to investigate these locations. He went to [[Switzerland]] himself and posed as a Flag Smasher, only to get beaten by [[Dovich]].
*'''Expert Hacker''': ''To be added''
*'''Multilingualism''': Torres is fluent in his native English, as well as Arabic and German.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''Handgun''': Torres used a handgun to try and arrest [[Dovich]] in [[Switzerland]].
* '''Dual Barrel Wrist-mounted Machine Gun''': The left gauntlet of Falcon's redesigned uniform utilizes a wrist-mounted dual emission machine gun controlled via clenching a fist. Falcon utilized this firearm against the three SERPENT members escaping with the canister.
* '''Wrist-mounted Miniature Rocket Launcher''': Falcon utilized a wrist-mounted miniature rocket launcher on his right bracer against the Japanese pilots.

===Other Equipment===
*'''Bulletproof Vest''': Torres wears this military vest as his standard armor. He used it while providing ground support for [[Sam Wilson]] during the [[Rescue of Captain Vassant|Rescue]] of Captain [[Vassant]].
{{Quote|Wait, yo, you forgot the [[EXO-7 Falcon|wings]]."<br>"Keep 'em.|Joaquín Torres and [[Sam Wilson]]|Truth}}
*'''[[EXO-7 Falcon]]''': After [[Sam Wilson]] took [[Captain America's Shield]] from [[John Walker]]'s possession, he gave the damaged EXO-7 Falcon over to Torres.
*'''Falcon Uniform''': ''To be added''

===Vehicles===
*'''[[Humvee]]''': Torres drove a Humvee while providing ground support for [[Sam Wilson]] during the [[Rescue of Captain Vassant|Rescue]] of Captain [[Vassant]].

